description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a passionate, dedicated and highly motivated Mental Health Nurse to work on Melissa Suite, 16 bedded Female Acute Unit based at The Oleaster Centre&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will act as a positive role model for staff in a manner that positively reflects the philosophy of the unit and the values of the organisation. This is an exciting opportunity for any Registered Mental Health Nurse interested and committed to delivering care within a safe, secure and therapeutic environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants must be able to work in a challenging and dynamic environment. You will need to demonstrate a range of skills including effective communication, empathy, self-awareness, and critical self-reflection skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we’d like from you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RMN Qualified willing to work in a busy challenging role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent understanding of Safeguarding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of Multidisciplinary Services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NMC (Nursing &amp; Midwifery Council Registered)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the Mental Health Act&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Patient centred &amp; commitment to delivering high quality care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organisational capability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility in approach to work and a strong &quot;can do&quot; attitude&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we’d like to give you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive Induction and commitment to on-going training care and support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development in your risk management and assessment skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development of leaderships skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personality Disorder training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Involvement in Positive Behavioural Support (PBS) plans with service users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicant must be able to work a full range of shifts, Early, Late, Nighst, Weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLuke OvertonJob titleWard ManagerEmail addressluke.overton@nhs.netTelephone number0121 301 2109 / 2103&lt;/p&gt;
